original: Johansson, Carl Fridolf, redaktör, Kungsbacka, f. 21/9/93 i Hanhals, Hall. 1., av Carl Johan J. o. Selma Josefina Christensson. G. 21 m. Anna Ingeborg Ifvarsson. Barn: Boris f. 22, Sten-Gösta 25, Gudrun 27, Ulla 30. — Olika anst. t. 21, red. f. tidn. Nordhalland ’sed. 21. Led. av stadsfullm. sed. 27, led. av drätsedkamm. 27-40 o. av folkskistyr. 25-35.
translated: Johansson, Carl Fridolf, editor, from Kungsbacka, born September 21, 1893 in Hanhals, Halland, the first child of Carl Johan J. and Selma Josefina Christensson. Married in 1921 to Anna Ingeborg Ifvarsson. They had four children: Boris born in 1922, Sten-Gösta born in 1925, Gudrun born in 1927, and Ulla born in 1930. He held various jobs up until 1921 when he became an editor for the newspaper Nordhalland, where he served until 1921. He was a member of the city council from 1927 and served on the finance and school committees from 1927-1940. He was also a member of the school board from 1925-1935.
